Petroleos Mexicanos Sells 10 Billion Pesos of Bonds After Postponing Sale

-- B y   C a r l o s   M a n u e l   R o d r i g u e z
-- 
2011-09-27T23:02:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/petroleos-mexicanos-sells-10-billion-pesos-of-bonds-after-postponing-sale.html
Petroleos Mexicanos sold 7 billion
pesos of floating-rate bonds maturing in 2017 and 3 billion
pesos of inflation-linked bonds maturing in 2021 today, the
company said on its website.  Corp. Actinver SAB and local units of HSBC Holdings Plc,
Banco Santander SA and Bank of America Corp. participated as
underwriters on the floating-rate bonds, the company said.  The funds raised will go toward refinancing and investment,
the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carlos Manuel Rodriguez in Mexico City at 
 carlosmr@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jonathan Roeder at 
 jroeder@bloomberg.net  